<div id="I_file">&lt;ios&gt; &lt;iostream&gt;</div>
<h1><span class="namespace" title="namespace std">std::</span><a href="/reference/ios/basic_ios/">basic_ios</a>::narrow</h1>
<div class="C_prototype"><pre>char narrow (char_type wc, char dfault) const;</pre></div><div id="I_description">Narrow character</div>
<section id="description">
Returns the transformation of character <var>wc</var> (generally, of a wide character type) to its equivalent of type <code>char</code>.<br>
<br>
This function returns the result of calling the <samp><a href="/ctype::narrow">ctype::narrow</a></samp> facet of the <samp><a href="/locale">locale</a></samp> object currently <i><a href="/basic_ios::imbue">imbued</a></i> in the stream.<br>
</section>
<br>
<section id="parameters">
<h3>Parameters</h3>
<dl>
<dt>wc</dt>
<dd>Wide character to be <i>narrowed</i>.<br>
Member type <samp>char_type</samp> is the type of characters used by the stream (i.e., its first class template parameter, <samp>charT</samp>).<br>
</dd>
<dt>dfault</dt>
<dd>Character returned if <var>wc</var> has no standard equivalent.</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<br>
<section id="return">
<h3>Return Value</h3>
The <code>char</code> equivalent of <var>c</var>.<br>
</section>
<br>
<section id="access">
<h3>Data races</h3>
Accesses the stream object.<br>
Concurrent access to the same stream object may cause data races.<br>
</section>
<br>
<section id="exceptions">
<h3>Exception safety</h3>
<b>Strong guarantee:</b> if an exception is thrown, there are no changes in the stream.<br>
</section>
<br>
